-- England's Batsman Morgan to Miss Cricket World Cup After Breaking Finger
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2011-02-08T15:11:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-08/england-s-eoin-morgan-to-miss-cricket-world-cup-after-breaking-his-finger.html
  England  batsman Eoin Morgan will miss
the cricket World Cup because of a broken middle finger on his
left hand.  Morgan, 24, sustained the injury during a one-game
international in Australia on Jan. 26, the England and Wales
Cricket Board said on its  website . He played in the next two
one-days before returning to the U.K. three days ago to see a
specialist.  Ravi Bopara will replace Morgan in England’s 15-man squad
for the World Cup, which will be played Feb. 19 to April 2 in
India, Bangladesh and  Sri Lanka . The 25-year-old was a member of
England’s team at the World Cup four years ago.  England plays its first  World Cup  game against the
Netherlands on Feb. 22 in Nagpur, India.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Bob Bensch in London at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at   celser@bloomberg.net . 